Survey of 900 children
The survey took place during the last school year and involved 900 students from the Czech primary schools.
It was the second edition of "Obesity is not a chance," supported by General Health Insurance and Unilever society.
Since the beginning, more than 12000 students from sixth to third have registered for this project.
One of the determinants that causes a dramatic increase in the number of overweight and even obese children is the absence of a correct diet and not enough physical exercise.
"Only half of the children questioned indicate, for example, eating 5 times a day breakfast in case - lunch - taste - dinner, which is a basic principle of good food," one of the results of the survey.
Without breakfast and carpentry at dinner
Specialists draw attention to the fact that for healthy development you need some basic details such as a family breakfast at the same time.
In Chequia, only 23% of the students' families eat at the same time.
In most families each takes his own breakfast.
And the worst that has been noted is that one tenth of the population does not take breakfast at all.
However, breakfast is the basis for a good daily diet.
The questionnaire showed that in the families of obese children unhealthy fries are more often consumed.
Almost every student - not to mention weight - drinks sweet drinks every day (70%).
More than 40% of the children questioned regularly sport but for parents it is half, only 15%.
Prepare your food
Another part of the survey allowed selected children (204 boys and 172 girls from 13 schools) to prepare their own food from opportunities offered according to their own taste and personal opinion.
"The preferences of Czech children between the ages of 12 and 15 are far from the ideal in terms of healthy eating."
Among their favorite dishes there are many cakes, meats and sucreries.
"The most alarming is in particular a great preference for sweet lemonades," is indicated in the survey results.
For lunch it was the pasta that took the first place right in front of the white meat.
Children did not want crickets at all and the preference for fish and vegetable meals was very low.
Health Cap
The survey also showed that children are ready to change their habits from the time they receive ad hoc information.
"During a review of a group of survey participants who had completed the questionnaire after the awareness session" Obesity is not a chance, "there was a determined willingness to move towards a healthy diet," says survey results.
The most important was for example with regard to sweet lemonades because children began to give preference to drinking water.
Children most often checked white meat and fish as a main dish and would reduce sweet dishes and "knedliky" (Czech speciality of bread flour or potatoes).
