The Velvet Students in concert with the choirs of Charles University
Festa Academica Festival offers for the third time festivities that link the International Student Day with the anniversary of the Velvet Revolution with a musical game.
During the festival there are 20 choirs from higher and secondary schools.
The nail of the festival is made up of two concerts orgned on 17 November.
"Charles University has an important part in this festival."
"Among the choirs there is the Choor of the Faculty of Pedagogia and Humanity, in the committee of the festival headquarters rector Vaclav Hampl," says the head of the organizing team Jakub Calou.
