FDI contraction
Apart from the decline in economic activity and the rise in unemployment, in 2011 the largest reduction in foreign direct investment over the past 10 years was recorded, according to the Economic Secretariat from January to June the State's FDI has reached $630 thousand 697, a decrease of 87.74 per cent compared to $5 million 143 thousand 312 recorded in the same period of the previous year.
