Interviewees on the possibility of "voting by vote," María de los Ángeles Llanänder said that with the approval of the relevant guidelines by the General Council of IEM it will be possible to achieve the partial and total counts of votes by the local electoral body.
For example, the partial count of votes, one or more electoral packages, may be that: the results of the minutes do not coincide; there is no ballot record and there is no record of the ballot box in the ballot box; or there are obvious errors or changes in the minutes.
In addition, the total count of votes received in all election polls may be made when there is an indication that the difference between the alleged winner of the respective election and the candidate who obtained second place in the election is equal to or below a percentage point; provided that at the beginning of the session there is an express petition of the party representative and / or coalition who presented the second of the reported candidates.
The total count of the vote may also be made if at the end of the common count it follows that the difference between the presumed winner and the second-place candidate is equal to or less than one percentage point, provided that there is the express petition of the representative of the political party whose second-out candidate, in which case the electoral packages that have been subject to the partial count will be excluded.
It should be mentioned that this is the situation of Morelia's election, where according to PREP, the difference between first and second place is only 0.16 per cent, even without counting the votes of 129 of the total 923 minutes.
