Thus was the work of the person of Cali who identified the corpse of Alfonso Cano
A typist from Cali has passed to history like the man who confirmed the death of "Alfonso Cano '.
The work of these officials is crucial.
The past November 4 a typist from Cali's ITC has passed to history as the person who confirmed the identity of the supreme leader of the Farc: "Alfonso Cano," confronting his fingerprints.
Of the seven typists working in the CTI local offices, this week it was the "availability 'turn of Eliazar González, a Puerto Tejada man who has been working in the field of judicial investigation for 21 years.
At the beginning of his career, González worked in Chocó's municipes, where many times he had to spend more than five days in the forest to reach the place in which the bodies were to be identified.
The year 2000 he was transferred to the capital of Valle and after having taken appropriate courses, he specialized in typing, which is the study of friction skin, that is, paumes and feet.
During the week of the operation against alias Alfonso Cano, Eliazar had been warned to take clothes with him for at least three days.
Something very big was waiting for him.
Friday night he left for Cauca in a Palmira helicopter.
He knew that he had to identify two corpses and that one of them was suspected to be that of the man who was leading the oldest guerrilla in the world, so he was asked to take the map with the ten fingerprints of Guillermo León Sáenz (his real name).
But when he arrived with the investigation team at the corpse, he did not recognize him by his physical aspect, because he was very different from that he had seen in the media.
He had no beard, he was dressed like a peasant in the area, without glasses and much skinny.
But the fingerprints don't lie.
Accompanied by a Weltonian wolf, ink, a breeder and lantern, Eliazar compared the fingerprints of the corpse with those of the map.
His eye did not cheat on him: it was "Alfonso Cano."
That same night, the man from Puerto Tejada was the leader who confirmed to the Minister of Defence, Juan Carlos Pinzón that yes, he was the supreme leader of the Farc.
Looking for the footprint
For a typist of Sijín de Cali, the recognition that President Juan Manuel Santos made to Eliazar González, in a press conference for the operation against "Cano," is very significant.
A lot of people don't know our job.
Dactyloscopy is an exact science, without margin of error, which can be crucial in the resolution of crimes.
Aside from identifying corpses, typists support investigations for crimes such as theft and homicide and confirm the identity of persons captured.
When captured, many offenders present false identity cards or do not have documents.
We take their fingerprints and look for them in the database.
The researcher argued that in a case of theft he had to remove part of a wall from a house, because in this place the thief had supported his hand to bring out a safe full of jewelry and money.
"The walls are difficult because they are not adequate areas to draw a fingerprint, but in this case we were able to get the fingerprint from all hands and identify the offender who had participated in different flights," he remembers.
The fingerprints may also remove or confirm suspects in cases of homicide.
Recently, we found a dead man with bottles of drink around him.
It was determined by the intercourse of the investigation that a parent may be suspect of the crime and indeed a imprint on the bottle coincided.
Even if it does not guarantee that he is the assassin, it places him on the scene of crime.
A CTI typist explained that "fingerprints of objects with chemical or physical reagents are extracted."
When they appear, a dryer or a strip is used to take them.
Subsequently, fingerprints are sent to Asif, the database of the declinents, or to the Civil National Register.
"The problem is that there are still many undocumented Colombians," said the expert from the ITC.
He explained that everything is not how it is shown in the CSI television program.
Like everything that shines is not gold, everything you touch does not become a strong footprint.
However, it can be used if the necessary confrontation is achieved.
