It is that there is a rather broad consensus between left and right.
On the right, the tone was given by Jacques Chirac who stated in 1976 that "900000 unemployed should not be a problem in a country with almost 2 million immigrant workers," and on the left, by Michel Rocard explaining that France "cannot host all the world's misery" in 1990.
The only difference, the degree of generosity
